poppler/pdftohtml

Note:

	As of 6/18, you must use clang/clang++ to build poppler due to a bug in gcc/g++ that causes it to fail building non-PIE binaries correctly. In this case, you need to use:
	"./configure --disable-shared CC=clang CXX=clang++ ...""
	
Install instructions:

	apt-get install libfontconfig1-dev
	tar -xzf poppler-0.22.5.tar.gz
	cd poppler-0.22.5/
	./configure --disable-shared CC=clang CXX=clang++ CFLAGS="-Wall -g -O2 -no-pie" CXXFLAGS="-Wall -Woverloaded-virtual -Wnon-virtual-dtor -Wcast-align -fno-exceptions -fno-check-new -fno-common -g -O2 -ansi -no-pie"
	make all

Running:
	
	afl-fuzz-saveinputs -i seed_dir -x pdf.dict -o out_dir -e 1440 -Q -- ./poppler-0.22.5/utils/pdftohtml @@
